comments.text: In my opinion, there was no dog. First off, I highly doubt that 2 young girls on a hike with a cute dog would not have taken pictures of and with the dog. Second, who would want the responsibility of taking someone else's dog on a hike in a jungle with potential predators and limitless opportunities for the dog to take off. Third, would you trust someone you barely know to take your dog out for a walk in a vast wilderness. And finally, I have heard of dogs finding their way back home, but supposedly these girls took a cab to their destination, which tells me that it probably would have been difficult if not impossible for the dog to orient itself in order to find it's way home if the site was so far they had to take a vehicle to get there.  This would mean that the dog story was concocted by the host family, and would infer that whatever befell the 2 girls, the host family was somehow involved. Just maybe everyone on the Panamanian end of this tragedy was directly involved.
comments.author: @36samson

comments.text: If the photos happened to be taken in the dark, the flash could serve as evidence of their location when, in a panicked, fast-moving, and survival instinct, they activated the camera's burst or automatic mode in the evening because they couldn't see anything. So where were they before?
